snippet: Rescuers dug with picks and shovels trying to reach dozens of people trapped under houses collapsed by a strong earthquake on Monday that shook a central island and set off landslides.
abstract: Rescuers in the Philippines continue to dig with picks and shovels trying to reach dozens of people trapped under houses collapsed by a strong earthquake that shook a central island and set off landslides; at least 13 people are killed and 40 are believed missing.
lead_paragraph: Rescuers dug with picks and shovels trying to reach dozens of people trapped under houses collapsed by a strong earthquake on Monday that shook a central island and set off landslides.

headline.main: Philippines: At Least 13 Killed in Quake
headline.print_headline: Philippines: At Least 13 Killed in Quake
